$ DOM example: document.getElementsByTagName

`document.getElementsByTagName('div')` returns an array of nodes whose HTML tags is → development/web/HTML/tags/div[`<div>`].

gh|about-Document-Object-Model|/Node/Document/getElementsByTagName.html||

sa:

  Two elements can be referenced more directly:
    • `document.documentElement` returns a document's → development/web/HTML/tags/html[`<html>`] element
    • `document.body` returns the → development/web/HTML/tags/body[`<body>`] element
  

  → development/web/DOM/examples/Node/Document/getElementById[`document.getElementById('…')`] returns the (single) element, if it exists, whose attribute `id` has a given value.

  → development/web/DOM/examples/Node/Document/getElementsByName[`document.getElementsByName('abc')`] returns an array of elements whose `name` attribute is `abc`.

  → development/web/DOM/examples[DOM examples]
